title: Planes, Trains & Automobiles
overview: A man must struggle to travel home for Thanksgiving with a lovable oaf of a shower curtain ring salesman as his only companion.

title: Crimes and Misdemeanors
overview: An ophthalmologist's mistress threatens to reveal their affair to his wife while a married documentary filmmaker is infatuated with another woman.

title: Withnail & I
overview: In 1969, two substance-abusing, unemployed actors retreat to the countryside for a holiday that proves disastrous.

title: The Royal Tenenbaums
overview: The eccentric members of a dysfunctional family reluctantly gather under the same roof for various reasons.

title: La dolce vita
overview: A series of stories following a week in the life of a philandering paparazzo journalist living in Rome.

title: Little Miss Sunshine
overview: A family determined to get their young daughter into the finals of a beauty pageant take a cross-country trip in their VW bus.

title: Captain Fantastic
overview: In the forests of the Pacific Northwest, a father devoted to raising his six kids with a rigorous physical and intellectual education is forced to leave his paradise and enter the world, challenging his idea of what it means to be a parent.

title: C.R.A.Z.Y.
overview: A young French-Canadian, growing up in the 1960s and 1970s, struggles to reconcile his emerging homosexuality with his father's conservative values and his own Catholic beliefs.

title: Modern Times
overview: The Tramp struggles to live in modern industrial society with the help of a young homeless woman.

title: La règle du jeu
overview: A bourgeois life in France at the onset of World War II, as the rich and their poor servants meet up at a French chateau.

title: Birdman or (The Unexpected Virtue of Ignorance)
overview: A washed-up superhero actor attempts to revive his fading career by writing, directing, and starring in a Broadway production.

title: The Station Agent
overview: When his only friend dies, a man born with dwarfism moves to rural New Jersey to live a life of solitude, only to meet a chatty hot dog vendor and a woman dealing with her own personal loss.

title: Me and Earl and the Dying Girl
overview: High schooler Greg, who spends most of his time making parodies of classic movies with his co-worker Earl, finds his outlook forever altered after befriending a classmate who has just been diagnosed with cancer.

title: Hannah and Her Sisters
overview: Between two Thanksgivings two years apart, Hannah's husband falls in love with her sister Lee, while her hypochondriac ex-husband rekindles his relationship with her sister Holly.

title: No Man's Land
overview: Bosnia and Herzegovina during 1993 at the time of the heaviest fighting between the two warring sides. Two soldiers from opposing sides in the conflict, Nino and Ciki, become trapped in no man's land, whilst a third soldier becomes a living booby trap.

title: Breakfast at Tiffany's
overview: A young New York socialite becomes interested in a young man who has moved into her apartment building, but her past threatens to get in the way.

title: Once Upon a Time... in Hollywood
overview: A faded television actor and his stunt double strive to achieve fame and success in the final years of Hollywood's Golden Age in 1969 Los Angeles.

title: Chung Hing sam lam
overview: Two melancholy Hong Kong policemen fall in love: one with a mysterious female underworld figure, the other with a beautiful and ethereal server at a late-night restaurant he frequents.

title: The Muppet Christmas Carol
overview: The Muppet characters tell their version of the classic tale of an old and bitter miser's redemption on Christmas Eve.

title: Night on Earth
overview: An anthology of 5 different cab drivers in 5 American and European cities and their remarkable fares on the same eventful night.
